2023-09-27

Tumor Information

Invasive Breast Carcinoma

The NCIt code is C9245

Access the CNV frequency data

load library

library(pgxRpi)

Access data

freq <- pgxLoader(type='frequency', output='pgxfreq', filters='NCIT:C9245')

The metadata information is

freq$meta
##         code                     label sample_count
## 1 NCIT:C9245 Invasive Breast Carcinoma         3796
## 2      total                                   3796

The data looks like this

freq$data$`NCIT:C9245`[c(1:3),]
##      filters reference_name   start     end gain_frequency loss_frequency no
## 1 NCIT:C9245              1       0  400000          2.397          1.159  1
## 2 NCIT:C9245              1  400000 1400000          4.083          7.877  2
## 3 NCIT:C9245              1 1400000 2400000          2.608          6.981  3

Visualization

pgxFreqplot(freq)

pgxFreqplot(freq, chrom=8)

pgxFreqplot(freq, chrom=c(1,3,8))

# Analysis

According to the plot, there are frequent duplication on chromosome 1q and 8q and frequent deletion on chromosomes 1p, 8p, 11q (25% as a cut-off). One Study detected frequent gains of ..p …p. ..p and losses in ..p …p …p There are overlaps for duplication ….., for deletion ….
